question: William has 100 square meters of strawberry field. There are 8 strawberrys per square meter. William can harvest his strawberrys every 2 months. How many strawberrys can William harvest within a year?
answer:
William has 8*100= <<8*100=800>>800 strawberrys on his field.
William can harvest his strawberrys 12 / 2 = <<12/2=6>>6 times per year
Therefore William can harvest 800*6 = <<800*6=4800>>4800 strawberrys per year.
#### 4800
